===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
''{{w|Shuowen}}'': {{Han compound|臀|alt1=𡱂|殳|ls=psc|c1=p|c2=s|t2=hand holding a weapon}} – the sound of hitting (not attested in ancient documents).

{{zh-ref|Chi (2010)}} considers the character to be developed from {{zh-l|*𠂤|buttocks}}; {{zh-l|*尸|body}} and {{zh-l|*丌|pedestal}} are added to form {{zh-l|*𡱂|buttocks}}, and {{zh-l|*殳}} is added to emphasize the meaning of “hitting the buttocks”.

===Etymology===
From {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*r-t(u/i)l||buttocks; heel; dull; blunt; rounded part}}. Compare {{cog|kac|shatin|sha'''tin'''|buttocks}}. Related to {{och-l|臀|buttocks}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}).

Whether “lofty building” is related is unclear; {{zh-ref|Chi (2010)}} suggests that it is a semantic extension of “buttocks”, which are elevated from the ground.

